synonyms: dvādaśa-māsera—of the twelve months; devatā—predominating Deities; ei—these; bāra jana—twelve Personalities of Godhead; mārga-śīrṣe—the month of Agrahāyana (November-December); keśava—Keśava; pauṣe—the month of Pauṣa (December-January); nārāyaṇa—Nārāyaṇa.
translation: "These twelve are the predominating Deities of the twelve months. Keśava is the predominating Deity of Agrahāyana, and Nārāyaṇa is the predominating Deity of Pauṣa.
